parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of Takata airbag recall parts can lead to a delay in the repair of the vehicle, potentially causing a risk to the driver and passengers in the event of an accident.
symptoms: None
as the issue is related to the unavailability of parts for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delay in Takata Airbag Recall Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in the Takata airbag recall repair can cause a risk to the driver and passengers in the event of an accident, as the faulty airbag may not deploy properly or may deploy with excessive force.
symptoms: None
as the issue is related to the delay in the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain and tensioner can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine light comes on
the vehicle stalls or fails to start
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle has difficulty accelerating
the vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
the vehicle shakes violently upon starting or when driving over 40 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, engine failure, and potentially cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
the oil light illuminates
the vehicle requires frequent oil additions
the vehicle has difficulty starting or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger can cause the engine to lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the vehicle has difficulty accelerating
the vehicle stalls or fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the check engine warning light to illuminate, leading to decreased engine performance and potentially causing damage to other engine components.
symptoms: The check engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle may experience decreased engine performance
and the catalytic converter may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the plastic water pump can cause coolant leaks, engine overheating, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The water pump breaks
coolant leaks
the "shut engine" light comes on
and the vehicle may overheat.
